HEADWORD: B-horizon
<hw>B-horizon</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>that layer of soil in a
well-developed soil lying immediately below the A-horizon, and which
contains deposits of organic matter leached from surface
soils.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> B horizon.</syn>⟦br⟧
